  + xharbour/source/rdd/dbdelim.prg
  + xharbour/source/rdd/dbjoin.prg
  + xharbour/source/rdd/dbsdf.prg
    * moved RDD related .prg files from rtl to rdd directory (library)
      Non GNU make files must be updated. I'd like to ask Marek or
      other Windows developers to borrow non GNU make files from Harbour
      to xHarbour. Now in Harbour there is only one list with dependences
      common.mak which is common for all other make systems and header
      files designed for given makes (currently two: makefile.bc, makefile.vc)
      They can create static build and DLLs. For changing file location,
      adding new ones or deleting some existing files needs only one file
      to be updated - one entry for each file. I'd like to see the same in
      xHarbour and only more header files if we want to support more non
      GNU make systems.

  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbcmd.c
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbfuncs.prg
